				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: LDON Augment for epic?<a name="50272"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 6 04 11:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Here is a link to a good listing of the cost, locations and type of the various procs you can add to your weapons. 
<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessage?topicID=19286.topic ">http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessage?topicID=19286.topic </a>
<br />

<br />
Proc damage has become a major component of my melee DPS. I bought WA5 and SF3 so I could get the most out of my procs. If you aren't in PoTime, then I suggest you get the poison and cold based procs. I like them. I have a Lava Infused Bludgeon in my main hand. It comes with a fire based proc and I augmented it to add a poison based proc. On my epic I put the 150 dd cold based proc. I am pleased with them. The fire based proc doesn't land much--if at all--in The Tower of Sol Ro or PoFire. The cold based proc doesn't land in PoWater. There are some mobs where the poison based proc won't land too. But all in all they all land pretty well.
<br />

<br />
Drumm
<br />

<br />
Edit: Can anyone explain how I can make that link work?
